# Feature Handoff Rule

When this is included in the chat session, generate a **short handoff for the feature currently in progress** — not a project overview.

## Scope

**Include only:**
- The active feature (name, goal, direction)
- That feature’s user flow (screens/steps, briefly)
- Files **for this feature only** (schema, screens, domain, storage, use-cases, doc)
- Incremental plan if work is step-by-step (done steps + **exact next step**)
- Recent progress on this feature (few bullets)
- Open items / decisions for this feature

**Do NOT include** (already in `CLAUDE.md`, `.cursor/rules/`, etc.):
- Stack, layer diagram, folder map of whole repo
- Global architecture, offline-first, V1, UI/domain rules
- Collaboration style, caveman mode, commit preferences
- Unrelated features (e.g. nadbar) unless they block this feature

Assume the next agent reads global rules first; handoff = **feature continuity only**.

---

# Handoff Structure (output)

## 1. Active Feature
- Name (Hebrew product name OK)
- One-line goal
- Overall direction for this feature

## 2. Feature Flow
- List → create → edit (or wizard steps) in user terms
- No global routing map

## 3. Feature Files
Bullet list of paths that matter **now** (read/edit). Example pattern:
- `src/screens/*Feature*Screen.tsx`
- `*Form.schema.ts`
- `src/domain/*`, `src/storage/*`, `src/useCases/*`
- `docs/*.md` if exists

## 4. Plan (if incremental refactor)
- Numbered steps user agreed on
- Mark completed steps
- **Next step** — one clear action for the next agent

## 5. Recent Progress
- 2–5 bullets max, this feature only
- Last session changes only

## 6. Open Items
- Pending steps, doc updates, product decisions
- Feature-scoped only

## 7. Feature Conventions (only if relevant)
- e.g. form schema refactor → keep `src/dev/seedMockData.ts` + `scripts/seed-localStorage.mjs` in sync, run `npm run seed`
- Do not repeat global conventions

---

# Output Style

- Compact, bullets, AI-friendly
- Stable between sessions **for the same feature**; rewrite when feature changes
- Next step must be actionable without re-reading full chat
- No changelog essay

